The paper deals with graph clustering, which is a topic in both computer science and applied mathematics. The use of effective resistance and low conductance sets suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.SI (social and information networks). The algorithmic nature of the paper and the focus on optimization suggest that it may also belong to cs.IT (information theory) and cs.NA (numerical analysis). Finally, the use of graphs and the study of their properties suggest that the paper may belong to cs.CG (computational geometry).
